Tic-Tac-Toe Game in Python:
Tic-Tac-Toe is a classic two-player game where players take turns marking a 3×3 grid with "X" or "O". The player who gets three marks in a row (horizontally, vertically, or diagonally) wins.

Description:
- Uses a 3×3 NumPy array to represent the board.
- Players input row and column to place their mark.
- Checks for a winner after each move.
- Ends in a draw if the board is full.
- Switches turns between "X" and "O".
